        • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

          Not sure where we went after Alexis' goal. The game started off like a training exercise and although the goal was fortunate in the way it came, it was deserved nonetheless. However, after about half an hour, we switched off. Even when we were in possession, we didn't look particularly penetrative and although I don't mind patient build-up, this looked more like we were waiting for Everton to present us with an opportunity rather than create the opportunity ourselves. That works with poor teams but Everton have some good players and Koeman is a good manager. You could see how he set up the team not to be overawed at the start but aggressive once they equalised, I would've hoped we'd nullify their aggressiveness by playing one-touch football, moving it quickly and getting them running. They aren't a team happy at doing that for large portions of the game a la Leverkusen/Liverpool. Not sure how Iwobi didn't score at the end but a point would've been fortunate. Need to beat City now.
